Commentary_short: Zampa to Abid Ali, 2 runs

Commentary: <b>clears the left leg<b>, and this time he nails the slog sweep, right into the gap
Commentary_short: Zampa to Abid Ali, FOUR runs

Commentary: three slog sweeps in a row, but he can't lay a bat on this one. Carey whips the bails off, and there's an appeal ... but it's for caught behind! The umpire says no, so Australia go upstairs for a review. But there's nothing on UltraEdge, so the decision will stand
Commentary_short: Zampa to Abid Ali, no run

Commentary: pushed back to the bowler
Commentary_short: Lyon to Mohammad Rizwan, no run

Commentary: Rizwan skips out and sends a drive skimming to cover, where it's stopped by Finch - but not quickly enough to stop the single
Commentary_short: Lyon to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run

Commentary: short third man tumbles to his left to stop a very late dab, just the single
Commentary_short: Lyon to Abid Ali, 1 run

Commentary: Rizwan fetches a sweep from outside off, another quick single
Commentary_short: Lyon to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run

Commentary: sliced very fine down towards third man, Khawaja sliding to keep the ball inside the rope down there. He dabbed it right off the stumps, very late
Commentary_short: Lyon to Abid Ali, 2 runs

Commentary: slapped through cover, one more
Commentary_short: Lyon to Abid Ali, 1 run

Commentary: a fantastic knock comes to an end! Abid gets down low to slog into the leg side, but slices under the ball to send a swirling chance out to Finch, who makes no mistake. It was a slightly tired looking shot. But he's put his team in a winning position on debut
Commentary_short: Zampa to Abid Ali, OUT
Dismissal_text: Abid Ali c Finch b Zampa 112 (119b 9x4 0x6) SR: 94.11

Commentary_short: Zampa to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run

Commentary: he comes forward and checks a drive to cover, who gets low to stop it
Commentary_short: Zampa to Umar Akmal, no run

Commentary: legbreak, and it grips a little as Umar gets forward again to defend
Commentary_short: Zampa to Umar Akmal, no run

Commentary: short, on off stump, and Umar cuts hard into the ground, the ball bouncing up to be stopped by point
Commentary_short: Zampa to Umar Akmal, no run

Commentary: too short again, and Umar's off the mark with a pull out to deep midwicket
Commentary_short: Zampa to Umar Akmal, 1 run

Commentary: a nicely-placed cut bounces out to the deep, behind square, and they're back for a second
Commentary_short: Maxwell to Umar Akmal, 2 runs

Commentary: well-placed again by Umar, angling a push to get the ball past a diving Khawaja at short third man
Commentary_short: Maxwell to Umar Akmal, 2 runs

Commentary: punched down to long on for a single
Commentary_short: Maxwell to Umar Akmal, 1 run

Commentary: eased down to long on, and the strike is turned over once more
Commentary_short: Maxwell to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run

Commentary: a sliced drive dribbles through point for one more
Commentary_short: Maxwell to Umar Akmal, 1 run

Commentary: this one slips out as a low full toss, and it's whipped through midwicket for two more
Commentary_short: Maxwell to Mohammad Rizwan, 2 runs

Commentary: played on! Coulter-Nile returns and strikes straight away. Umar was looking to get after him, swinging wildly into the leg side, but the under edge instead sends the ball onto his own stumps. Could there be a twist in the tail? This isn't an easy track to start on
Commentary_short: Coulter-Nile to Umar Akmal, OUT

Commentary: enter Saad Ali, who is also on his debut. He's off the mark straight away, nudging off his pads and calling Rizwan through for a hard-run two
Commentary_short: Coulter-Nile to Saad Ali, 2 runs

Commentary: chopped down through gully, but Maxwell dives at backward point to stop the run
Commentary_short: Coulter-Nile to Saad Ali, no run

Commentary: angled, but finer this time, and there's an easy single to third man
Commentary_short: Coulter-Nile to Saad Ali, 1 run

Commentary: Coulter-Nile aims full, and it's dug out through mid on
Commentary_short: Coulter-Nile to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run

Commentary: full and straight, Coulter-Nile stopping it in his follow through as it's pushed back at him
Commentary_short: Coulter-Nile to Saad Ali, no run

Commentary: appeal for lbw as Rizwan misses a sweep and his hit on the pad, but the umpire's not convinced. Maxwell floated that one up really high
Commentary_short: Maxwell to Mohammad Rizwan, no run

Commentary: flatter, shorter, and it's punched through cover
Commentary_short: Maxwell to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run

Commentary: another appeal! Saad is hit on the pad as he looks to glance, but it looked like the ball was headed down the leg side anyway
Commentary_short: Maxwell to Saad Ali, 1 leg bye

Commentary: a late cut sends the ball bouncing to backward point
Commentary_short: Maxwell to Mohammad Rizwan, no run

Commentary: chopped hard through cover, and there's an immediate call for two. It's a good call, and they're back safely
Commentary_short: Maxwell to Mohammad Rizwan, 2 runs

Commentary: another sweep, and Zampa fumbles his stop at short fine leg ... but they opt not to run off the misfield
Commentary_short: Maxwell to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run

Commentary: glanced to midwicket, into the gap
Commentary_short: Coulter-Nile to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run

Commentary: Saad steps into a crunchy drive, and he wants two but he's sent back. It would have been very tight
Commentary_short: Coulter-Nile to Saad Ali, 1 run

Commentary: short of a length, just outside off, and Rizwan slugs a front-foot pull out to midwicket, moving into the 90s
Commentary_short: Coulter-Nile to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run

Commentary: a firm drive finds mid off
Commentary_short: Coulter-Nile to Saad Ali, no run

Commentary: worked neatly off the hip, the ball bouncing out to deep square leg
Commentary_short: Coulter-Nile to Saad Ali, 1 run

Commentary: nice yorker from Coulter-Nile, and it's backed up by Maxwell at point, who dives to stop the ball as it's dug out square
Commentary_short: Coulter-Nile to Mohammad Rizwan, no run

Commentary: punched down the ground for one
Commentary_short: Maxwell to Saad Ali, 1 run

Commentary: Maxwell lobs a full one up on a leg stump line, from around the wicket, and Rizwan sweeps down to fine leg. It's placed well enough for a second run. Quick running
Commentary_short: Maxwell to Mohammad Rizwan, 2 runs

Commentary: paddled fine, and Pakistan find a vital boundary! Maxwell fired this one in quicker, but Rizwan was waiting for it with another paddle sweep, getting it fine of Zampa and hitting it well enough for the ball to beat him to the boundary
Commentary_short: Maxwell to Mohammad Rizwan, FOUR runs

Commentary: he's down the track to get to the pitch, working down to long on
Commentary_short: Maxwell to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run

Commentary: Saad comes down the track and is almost beaten behind his legs, but gets some pad on it to find a leg bye
Commentary_short: Maxwell to Saad Ali, 2 leg byes

Commentary: Saad spots some width, slicing it square for a single to keep the strike, 11 off the over
Commentary_short: Maxwell to Saad Ali, 1 run

Commentary: Saad falls! He was looking for a big pick-up shot over the leg side, but didn't connect well. Richardson holds a simple chance in the deep. Is panic setting in?
Commentary_short: Coulter-Nile to Saad Ali, OUT
Dismissal_text: Saad Ali c Richardson b Coulter-Nile 7 (12b 0x4 0x6) SR: 58.33

Commentary: swatted uppishly into the leg side, but falling safely in front of the fielder
Commentary_short: Coulter-Nile to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run

Commentary: Imad whips a length delivery out to one of the three at deep midwicket
Commentary_short: Coulter-Nile to Imad Wasim, 1 run

Commentary: very full, on off stump, and Rizwan goes to 99 by driving down to long on
Commentary_short: Coulter-Nile to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run

Commentary: punched firmly back at the bowler, who can't quite get down quickly enough to stop it, but Lyon comes around from mid off to ensure it's another dot
Commentary_short: Coulter-Nile to Imad Wasim, no run

Commentary: Imad backs away and rifles a shot into the off side, but he can't beat Lyon at mid off
Commentary_short: Coulter-Nile to Imad Wasim, no run

Commentary: short, outside off, and it's slapped hard out to the sweeper for Rizwan to raise his second hundred of the series. And this is only the second time that two Pakistan batsmen have scored ODI hundreds in the same chase
Commentary_short: Richardson to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run

Commentary: big swish outside off, but he hits only fresh air!
Commentary_short: Richardson to Imad Wasim, no run

Commentary: caught at deep point! Imad backs away and hacks at a slower bouncer. He can't get any distance on the shot though, and can't control it either. Marsh comes in off the boundary and holds a simple catch, Australia grab another!
Commentary_short: Richardson to Imad Wasim, OUT
Dismissal_text: Imad Wasim c Marsh b Richardson 1 (5b 0x4 0x6) SR: 20.00

Commentary: another play and a miss! Richardson is opting for a short-pitched approach, and Rizwan just cut underneath it
Commentary_short: Richardson to Mohammad Rizwan, no run

Commentary: this will help a little, Rizwan sprinting down the track and flat-batting another short one straight back over Richardson's head
Commentary_short: Richardson to Mohammad Rizwan, FOUR runs

Commentary: on a length, straight, and Rizwan is furious with himself as he can only push it back to the bowler. He was looking for a single to keep the strike
Commentary_short: Richardson to Mohammad Rizwan, no run

Commentary: just short of a good length, Yasir slugging it straight down the ground. Long on cleans up, and they only take a single
Commentary_short: Stoinis to Yasir Shah, 1 run

Commentary: an attempted slower bouncer goes awry, looping way down the leg side
Commentary_short: Stoinis to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 wide

Commentary: caught at deep backward square! It was pitched up, on his legs, and Rizwan actually got an excellent connection on this pick-up over the leg side. But he picked out Handscomb precisely in that position
Commentary_short: Stoinis to Mohammad Rizwan, OUT
Dismissal_text: Mohammad Rizwan c Handscomb b Stoinis 104 (102b 9x4 1x6) SR: 101.96

Commentary: short, rising over off stump, and Yasir can only pull to long on
Commentary_short: Stoinis to Yasir Shah, 1 run

Commentary: slammed over long off! It was just a good old fashioned slog, but it's cleared the fielder at the boundary to keep Pakistan hoping
Commentary_short: Stoinis to Usman Shinwari, SIX runs

Commentary: another slog, but this one is caught! It was the slow bouncer, and Shinwari tried to smash it over midwicket. But he got more height than distance, and Handscomb holds another catch. Barring anything silly from Australia, this match is now sealed
Commentary_short: Stoinis to Usman Shinwari, OUT
Dismissal_text: Usman Shinwari c Handscomb b Stoinis 6 (2b 0x4 1x6) SR: 300.00

Commentary: another slow bouncer, it's pulled out to deep square leg, and that's the game
Commentary_short: Stoinis to Yasir Shah, 1 run
